definition: not enough time (to do sth)/too late (to do sth)
to overtake/to catch up with/to hurry/to rush/to try to catch (the bus etc)/to drive (cattle etc) forward/to drive (sb) away/to avail oneself of (an opportunity)/until

sentences.english: Was a pity very much that the pigeon misses, has the matter not to be able frequently to come.
sentences.chinese: 很可惜，鴿子趕不及回來，常常有事不能來。

sentences.english: Are we too late for the printer' s deadline?
sentences.chinese: 我們趕不及印刷商的最後期限了嗎？
